                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            
                            <origDate when="1730" evidence="reign">From the subscriptions on f. 106r and 119v it appears that 
                                the Ms. was written in the last year of the reign of  ʿAḍma Giyorgis or <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2377Bakaffa">
                                    Bakāffā</persName>, and the first year of the reign of his successor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5617IyasuII">
                                        ʾIyāsu II</persName>., i. e. in  <date>AD 1730</date>, by one <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11366Qirqos">Qirqos or Cyriacus</persName>, for 
                                one <persName role="patron" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11364Isayeyas">Isaiah</persName>.
                            </origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area, 
                            from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. It was then looted 
                            by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.</provenance>
                    </history>
